  "root_text": {
    "dhp76:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp76:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp76:0.3": "Paṇḍitavagga ",
    "dhp76:0.4": "Rādhattheravatthu ",
    "dhp76:1": "Nidhīnaṁva pavattāraṁ, ",
    "dhp76:2": "yaṁ passe vajjadassinaṁ; ",
    "dhp76:3": "Niggayhavādiṁ medhāviṁ, ",
    "dhp76:4": "tādisaṁ paṇḍitaṁ bhaje; ",
    "dhp76:5": "Tādisaṁ bhajamānassa, ",
    "dhp76:6": "seyyo hoti na pāpiyo. ",
    "dhp77:0": "Assajipunabbasukavatthu ",
    "dhp77:1": "Ovadeyyānusāseyya, ",
    "dhp77:2": "asabbhā ca nivāraye; ",
    "dhp77:3": "Satañhi so piyo hoti, ",
    "dhp77:4": "asataṁ hoti appiyo. ",
    "dhp78:0": "Channattheravatthu ",
    "dhp78:1": "Na bhaje pāpake mitte, ",
    "dhp78:2": "na bhaje purisādhame; ",
    "dhp78:3": "Bhajetha mitte kalyāṇe, ",
    "dhp78:4": "bhajetha purisuttame. ",
    "dhp79:0": "Mahākappinattheravatthu ",
    "dhp79:1": "Dhammapīti sukhaṁ seti, ",
    "dhp79:2": "vippasannena cetasā; ",
    "dhp79:3": "Ariyappavedite dhamme, ",
    "dhp79:4": "sadā ramati paṇḍito. ",
    "dhp80:0": "Paṇḍitasāmaṇeravatthu ",
    "dhp80:1": "Udakañhi nayanti nettikā, ",
    "dhp80:2": "Usukārā namayanti tejanaṁ; ",
    "dhp80:3": "Dāruṁ namayanti tacchakā, ",
    "dhp80:4": "Attānaṁ damayanti paṇḍitā. ",
    "dhp81:0": "Lakuṇḍakabhaddiyattheravatthu ",
    "dhp81:1": "Selo yathā ekaghano, ",
    "dhp81:2": "vātena na samīrati; ",
    "dhp81:3": "Evaṁ nindāpasaṁsāsu, ",
    "dhp81:4": "na samiñjanti paṇḍitā. ",
    "dhp82:0": "Kāṇamātāvatthu ",
    "dhp82:1": "Yathāpi rahado gambhīro, ",
    "dhp82:2": "vippasanno anāvilo; ",
    "dhp82:3": "Evaṁ dhammāni sutvāna, ",
    "dhp82:4": "vippasīdanti paṇḍitā. ",
    "dhp83:0": "Pañcasatabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp83:1": "Sabbattha ve sappurisā cajanti, ",
    "dhp83:2": "Na kāmakāmā lapayanti santo; ",
    "dhp83:3": "Sukhena phuṭṭhā atha vā dukhena, ",
    "dhp83:4": "Na uccāvacaṁ paṇḍitā dassayanti. ",
    "dhp84:0": "Dhammikattheravatthu ",
    "dhp84:1": "Na attahetu na parassa hetu, ",
    "dhp84:2": "Na puttamicche na dhanaṁ na raṭṭhaṁ; ",
    "dhp84:3": "Na iccheyya adhammena samiddhimattano, ",
    "dhp84:4": "Sa sīlavā paññavā dhammiko siyā. ",
    "dhp85:0": "Dhammassavanattheravatthu ",
    "dhp85:1": "Appakā te manussesu, ",
    "dhp85:2": "ye janā pāragāmino; ",
    "dhp85:3": "Athāyaṁ itarā pajā, ",
    "dhp85:4": "tīramevānudhāvati. ",
    "dhp86:1": "Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte, ",
    "dhp86:2": "dhamme dhammānuvattino; ",
    "dhp86:3": "Te janā pāramessanti, ",
    "dhp86:4": "maccudheyyaṁ suduttaraṁ. ",
    "dhp87:0": "Pañcasataāgantukabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp87:1": "Kaṇhaṁ dhammaṁ vippahāya, ",
    "dhp87:2": "Sukkaṁ bhāvetha paṇḍito; ",
    "dhp87:3": "Okā anokamāgamma, ",
    "dhp87:4": "Viveke yattha dūramaṁ. ",
    "dhp88:1": "Tatrābhiratimiccheyya, ",
    "dhp88:2": "hitvā kāme akiñcano; ",
    "dhp88:3": "Pariyodapeyya attānaṁ, ",
    "dhp88:4": "cittaklesehi paṇḍito. ",
    "dhp89:1": "Yesaṁ sambodhiyaṅgesu, ",
    "dhp89:2": "sammā cittaṁ subhāvitaṁ; ",
    "dhp89:3": "Ādānapaṭinissagge, ",
    "dhp89:4": "anupādāya ye ratā; ",
    "dhp89:5": "Khīṇāsavā jutimanto, ",
    "dhp89:6": "te loke parinibbutā. ",
    "dhp89:7": "Paṇḍitavaggo chaṭṭho. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp76:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp76:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 76–89 ",
    "dhp76:0.3": "6. The Astute ",
    "dhp76:1": "Regard one who sees your faults ",
    "dhp76:2": "as a guide to a hidden treasure. ",
    "dhp76:3": "Stay close to one so wise and astute ",
    "dhp76:4": "who corrects you when you need it. ",
    "dhp76:5": "Sticking close to such an impartial person, ",
    "dhp76:6": "things get better, not worse. ",
    "dhp77:1": "Advise and instruct; ",
    "dhp77:2": "curb wickedness: ",
    "dhp77:3": "for you shall be loved by the good, ",
    "dhp77:4": "and disliked by the bad. ",
    "dhp78:1": "Don’t mix with bad friends, ",
    "dhp78:2": "nor with the worst of men. ",
    "dhp78:3": "Mix with spiritual friends, ",
    "dhp78:4": "and with the best of men. ",
    "dhp79:1": "Through joy in the teaching you sleep at ease, ",
    "dhp79:2": "with clear and confident heart. ",
    "dhp79:3": "An astute person always delights in the teaching ",
    "dhp79:4": "proclaimed by the Noble One. ",
    "dhp80:1": "Irrigators guide water, ",
    "dhp80:2": "fletchers straighten arrows, ",
    "dhp80:3": "carpenters carve timber, ",
    "dhp80:4": "the astute tame themselves. ",
    "dhp81:1": "As the wind cannot stir ",
    "dhp81:2": "a solid mass of rock, ",
    "dhp81:3": "so too blame and praise ",
    "dhp81:4": "do not affect the wise. ",
    "dhp82:1": "Like a deep lake, ",
    "dhp82:2": "clear and unclouded, ",
    "dhp82:3": "so clear are the astute ",
    "dhp82:4": "when they hear the teachings. ",
    "dhp83:1": "True persons give up everything, ",
    "dhp83:2": "they don’t cajole for the things they desire. ",
    "dhp83:3": "Though touched by sadness or happiness, ",
    "dhp83:4": "the astute appear neither depressed nor elated. ",
    "dhp84:1": "Never wish for success by unjust means, ",
    "dhp84:2": "for your own sake or that of another, ",
    "dhp84:3": "desiring children, wealth, or nation; ",
    "dhp84:4": "rather, be virtuous, wise, and just. ",
    "dhp85:1": "Few are those among humans ",
    "dhp85:2": "who cross to the far shore. ",
    "dhp85:3": "The rest just run around ",
    "dhp85:4": "on the near shore. ",
    "dhp86:1": "When the teaching is well explained, ",
    "dhp86:2": "those who practice accordingly ",
    "dhp86:3": "will cross over ",
    "dhp86:4": "Death’s dominion so hard to pass. ",
    "dhp87:1": "Rid of dark qualities, ",
    "dhp87:2": "an astute person should develop the bright. ",
    "dhp87:3": "Leaving home behind ",
    "dhp87:4": "for the seclusion so hard to enjoy, ",
    "dhp88:1": "try to find satisfaction there, ",
    "dhp88:2": "having left behind sensual pleasures. ",
    "dhp88:3": "Owning nothing, an astute person ",
    "dhp88:4": "would cleanse themselves of mental corruptions. ",
    "dhp89:1": "Those whose minds are rightly developed ",
    "dhp89:2": "in the awakening factors; ",
    "dhp89:3": "who, letting go of attachments, ",
    "dhp89:4": "delight in not grasping: ",
    "dhp89:5": "with defilements ended, brilliant, ",
    "dhp89:6": "they are quenched in this world. "
  },
